Summary
When the RGB Video component???s width/height attributes are set above 256 (e.g. 512??512), only the top-left 256??256 region updates. The rest of the screen never draws.

Steps to Reproduce

Place RGB Video (Input/Output library) in a circuit.

Set width=512, height=512.

Drive X, Y, DATA, CLK, WE to draw pixels beyond x=255 or y=255.

Observe that pixels outside the 256??256 area are clipped.

Expected Behavior
RGB Video should draw across the full configured width ?? height.

Actual Behavior
Drawing is clipped to 256??256 regardless of attributes.

Root Cause
com.cburch.logisim.std.io.Video#getState always creates a BufferedImage(256, 256, ???) and never reallocates it when attributes change.

Proposed Fix

Allocate the backing BufferedImage using the current WIDTH_OPTION and HEIGHT_OPTION, and recreate it when attributes change.
Patch (Video.java)

private State getState(CircuitState circuitState) {
-  var state = (State) circuitState.getData(this);
-  if (state == null) {
-    state = new State(new BufferedImage(256, 256, BufferedImage.TYPE_INT_ARGB));
-    circuitState.setData(this, state);
-  }
-  return state;
+  var state = (State) circuitState.getData(this);
+  final var attrs = getAttributeSet();
+  final int w = attrs.getValue(WIDTH_OPTION);
+  final int h = attrs.getValue(HEIGHT_OPTION);
+
+  if (state == null || state.img.getWidth() != w || state.img.getHeight() != h) {
+    final var newImg = new BufferedImage(w, h, BufferedImage.TYPE_INT_ARGB);
+    if (state != null && state.img != null) {
+      var gCopy = newImg.getGraphics();
+      gCopy.drawImage(state.img, 0, 0, null);
+      gCopy.dispose();
+    }
+    state = new State(newImg);
+    circuitState.setData(this, state);
+  }
+  return state;
}

Also adjust reset color for consistency:
- g.setColor(Color.YELLOW);
+ g.setColor(Color.BLACK);

Impact

Fixes broken rendering when WIDTH/HEIGHT > 256 (e.g. 512??512).

No regressions for smaller sizes.

Tested manually: 512??512 now works fully.

