### Describe the Bug

Several ioctls can leak resources if `copy_to_user()` fails after committing the resource. These are practically unreachable since the same pointer validated by `copy_from_user()` earlier in the ioctl will almost certainly succeed in `copy_to_user()`, but they should still be fixed.


### Example: `ioctl_pin_pages`

```c
pinning->page_count = nr_pages;
pinning->pages = pages;
pinning->dma_mapping = dma_mapping;
pinning->virtual_address = in.virtual_address;
pinning->outbound_iatu_region = iatu_region;

list_add(&pinning->list, &priv->pinnings);  // Resource committed
mutex_unlock(&priv->mutex);

out.noc_address = noc_address;
if (clear_user(&arg->out, in.output_size_bytes) != 0)
    return -EFAULT;  // BUG: pages still pinned, iATU region leaked

if (copy_to_user(&arg->out, &out, bytes_to_copy) != 0)
    return -EFAULT;  // BUG: same leak
```

